\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Bol Processor 2.9.7 beta Read Me\

\fs24 January 18, 2010\

\b0 \
Bol Processor is a program for music composition and improvisation with real-time MIDI, MIDI file, and Csound output.  It produces music from a set of rules (a compositional grammar) or from text scores typed or captured from a MIDI instrument.  Bol Processor 2 began as a shareware application for Macintosh computers developed by Bernard Bel and Srikumar Karaikudi Subramanian.  The original Bol Processor program was developed by Bernard Bel and Jim Kippen on an Apple IIc.\
\
Bol Processor 2 is now distributed as free software (open source) under a BSD-style license (please see the License.txt file for complete terms).  BP development is hosted by Sourceforge at <{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://bolprocessor.sourceforge.net/"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 http://bolprocessor.sourceforge.net/}}>.  Developers interested in joining the project are most welcome to do so.  Please email us for more information.\
\
This package contains a beta release of Bol Processor 2.9.7 for Mac OS X.  Full documentation and a set of examples is included with this package.  This is a beta release because recent changes have not been sufficiently tested for us to feel confident that they are working as intended.  As such, you may come across significant bugs of which we are not yet aware.  We would greatly appreciate your help in identifying any problems with this release.  Even though there may be (more) bugs (than usual), we feel that the changes in this release are important enough that most users will want to use it.\
\

\b\fs26 Important Changes in this Version\

\b0\fs24 \

\b Bol Processor is now a "universal binary".
\b0   This means that it runs natively on all Mac OS X computers (with either an Intel or PowerPC processor).  We are aware of a problem with BP2's graphics on Intel Macs (see 
\b Known Issues.rtf)
\b0 .  There may still be other problems from the conversion to Intel Macs, so let us know if you encounter any.\
\

\b This beta release requires Mac OS X 10.4 or later
\b0  to run whereas previous releases ran on 10.2 or later.  It should still be possible to compile BP for 10.2 or 10.3 but it is more work to make a universal binary that supports those versions and we have not yet completed that task.  Please let us know if you are still using OS X 10.2 or 10.3, otherwise we may conclude that there is no interest.  In the meantime, BP 2.9.6 fully supports 10.2 or later.\

\b\fs26 \

\fs24 This version is no longer compatible with the "Classic" Mac OS (Mac OS 9 and earlier).  
\b0 Please use BP 2.9.6 if you need Classic support.  
