\b\fs26 Installing Bol Processor on OS X\

\b0\fs24 \
There are no special installation requirements other than a minimum system version of OS X 10.4.  You can just drag the Bol Processor application wherever you like onto your hard drive.  You can also copy the documentation and example files wherever you would like.\
\
QuickTime MIDI instruments are not available via CoreMIDI.  To use your Mac's internal speaker for playback, you will need to install and run a software synthesizer.  A good free one is SimpleSynth by Pete Yandell.  You can download SimpleSynth from <{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://notahat.com/simplesynth"}}{\fldrslt http://notahat.com/simplesynth}}>.  For Midi input without an external keyboard, we recommend MidiKeys by Chris Reed.  You can download MidiKeys from <{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.manyetas.com/creed/midikeys.html"}}{\fldrslt http://www.manyetas.com/creed/midikeys.html}}>.\
\

\b\fs26 Obtaining Help for Bol Processor\

\b0\fs24 \
Bol Processor comes with a comprehensive Quick-start Guide and Reference Manual in HTML format that you can read with any web browser.  In addition, BP2 documents most items with a built-in help system: just press the Help key or Command-? and the mouse cursor will change to a question mark.  Then click on any button or label, choose any menu item, or select words in any text window and BP2 will display help on that item.  Browsing through the many included example files can also be a good way to learn about new concepts.\
\
For additional assistance and information, there is a forum for general discussion of Bol Processor at <{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?forum_id=555616"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 http://sourceforge.net/forum/forum.php?forum_id=555616}}> and a developer mailing list at <{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://lists.sourceforge.net/mailman/listinfo/bolprocessor-devel"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 http://lists.sourceforge.net/mailman/listinfo/bolprocessor-devel}}> \'97 both hosted by the Sourceforge project.  Regular announcements are posted on a special "read-only" announcement list: <{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://lists.sourceforge.net/mailman/listinfo/bolprocessor-announce"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 http://lists.sourceforge.net/mailman/listinfo/bolprocessor-announce}}>.\
\
A shared space for documentation and users' feedback is available on the website <{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://crdo.fr/phpwiki/index.php?pagename=BolProcessor"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 http://crdo.fr/phpwiki/index.php?pagename=BolProcessor}}\cf2 >.  \cf0 Anyone can create a user login and contribute.\
\
Finally, you can contact the developers of Bol Processor at the email addresses given near the end of this file.\
